						               													<description>A roll-and-move game based on the cartoon series &amp;quot;The Country Mouse and the City Mouse Adventures&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;The aim of this cooperative children's game is to lead all 4 pawns through the story of the stolen diamond and to solve the case together with Emily, Alexander and Sherlock Mouse before Notail Nogoodnik, the thief, is seen five times.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board shows a track consisting of lots of coloured spaces and pictures from the cartoon series. There are four pawns. Players take turns rolling the colour die. The active player moves a pawn of his/her choice to the next space of the colour on the die roll (all players can move all pawns). If a pawn lands on a yellow space, one of the twenty, randomly distributed face-down tiles has to be turned over. If it shows a picture from the board, the pawn is moved to the corresponding space. If the tile shows Notail Nogoodnik, it stays face-up and the player's turn is over.&amp;#10;To get a pawn to the finish line, the spaces has to be reached exactly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If all four player pawns reach the finish line, all players win together. If five tiles showing Notail Nogoodnik are turned over, they all lose together.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
